 Smith (American politician)|Malcolm Smith]]<br><small>(acting)</small>\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|data-sort-value=\"Espada, Pedro\"|[[Pedro Espada Jr.]]<br><small>(acting)</small>{{efn|Espada was a Democrat, but combined with the Republicans in a change of leadership which triggered the [[2009 New York State Senate leadership crisis]].}}\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|data-sort-value=\"Ravitch, Richard\"|[[Richard Ravitch]]<br><small>(Contested)</small>{{efn|Ravitch was appointed on July 8, 2009, but the appointment was contested in the courts. On August 20, the [[New York Supreme Court, Appellate Division|Appellate Division]] rejected the appointment, and Ravitch vacated the office.}}\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|data-sort-value=\"Smith, Malcolm\"|[[Malcolm Smith (American politician)|Malcolm Smith]]<br><small>(acting)</small>{{efn|Smith succeeded Espada on July 9 as [[Majority Leader of the New York State Senate|temporary President of the New York State Senate]], and claimed to be Acting Lieutenant Governor under the provisions of the New York State Constitution while the appointment of Ravitch was contested.}}\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|data-sort-value=\"Ravitch, Richard\"|[[Richard Ravitch]]{{efn|On September 22, the [[New York Court of Appeals]] reversed the Appellate Division's ruling, and thus re-instated Ravitch to the lieutenant governorship, beginning on July 8.}}\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|rowspan=\"3\"|56\n|rowspan=\"3\" data-sort-value=\"Cuomo, Andrew\"|[[File:Andrew Cuomo by Pat Arnow cropped.jpeg|75px]]\n!rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"row\"|[[Andrew Cuomo]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|{{dts|January 1, 2011}}<br />\u2013<br />''Incumbent''\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n|[[New York gubernatorial election, 2010|2010]]\n|data-sort-value=\"Duffy, Robert\"|[[Robert Duffy (politician)|Robert Duffy]]\n|- style=\"height:2em;\"\n|[[New York gubernatorial election, 2014|2014]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"Hochul, Kathy\"|[[Kathy Hochul]]\n|- 