gn=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.historycentral.com/bio/people/Harriman.html | title=Averell Harriman | publisher=HistoryCenteral.com | accessdate=July 12, 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Nelson Rockefeller]]\n|align=\"center\"|1959&ndash;1973\n|\n|\n|Vice President of the United States\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web | url=http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=r000363 | title=Rockefeller, Nelson Aldrich | work=Biographical Directory of the United States Congress | publisher=Clerk of the United States House of Representatives and Historian of the United States Senate | date= July 12, 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Hugh Carey]]\n|align=\"center\"|1975&ndash;1982\n|align=\"center\"|H\u2020\n|\n|\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web | url=http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=C000143 | title=Carey, Hugh Leo | work=Biographical Directory of the United States Congress | publisher=Clerk of the United States House of Representatives and Historian of the United States Senate | date= March 28, 2008}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Andrew Cuomo]]\n|align=\"center\"|2011&mdash;\n|\n|\n|[[United States Secretary of Housing and Urban Development|U.S. Secretary of Housing and Urban Development]]\n|\n|}\n\n==Living former Governors of New York==\n{{As of|2018|9}}, there are three living former Governors of New York, the oldest being [[George Pataki]] (served from 1995 to 2006, born 1945). The most recent governor to die was [[Mario Cuomo]] (served from 1983 to 1994, born 1932), on January 1, 2015; he is also the most recently serving governor to have died.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Governor\n!Gubernatorial term\n!Date of birth (and age)\n|-\n|[[George Pataki]]\n|align=\"center\"|1995&ndash;2006\n|{{birth date and age|1945|6|24}}\n|-\n|[[Eliot Spitzer]]\n|align=\"center\"|2007&ndash;2008\n|{{birth date and age|1959|6|10}}\n|-\n|[[David Paterson]]\n|align=\"center\"|2008&ndash;2010\n|{{birth date and age|1954|5|20}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[New York gubernatorial elections]]\n*[[List of colonial governors of New York]]\n\n==Notes==\n\n{{notelist|2}}\n\n==References==\n\n;General\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.ny.gov/governor/nygovs/index.html |title=Governors of New York |publisher=State of New York |accessdate=March 28, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080315162911/http://www.ny.gov/governor/nygovs/index.html |archivedate=March 15, 2008 }}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.nga.org/portal/site/nga/menuitem.8fd3d12ab65b304f8a278110501010a0?submit=Submit&State=NY |title=Governors Database: New York |year=2008 |work=National Governors Association |publisher=[[National Governors Association]] |accessdate=March 28, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071101022753/http://www.nga.org/portal/site/nga/menuitem.8fd3d12ab65b304f8a278110501010a0?submit=Submit&State=NY |archivedate=November 1, 2007 }}\n*{{cite book | last=Jenkins | first=John Stilwell | title=Lives of the Governors of the State of New York | publisher=[[James Cephas Derby|Derby and Miller]] | year=1851 | location=Auburn N.Y. | page=862 | url=http://cdl.library.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/moa/moa-cgi?notisid=ANW1479}}\n{{refend}}\n\n;Constitutions\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.dos.state.ny.us/info/constitution.htm |title=New York Constitution |publisher=New York Department of State |accessdate=July 12, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100723110017/http://www.dos.state.ny.us/info/constitution.htm |archivedate=July 23, 2010 }}\n*{{cite web | url=http://www.nycourts.gov/history/constitutions/1777_constitution.htm | title=1777 New York Constitution of New York | publisher=The Historical Society of the Courts of the State of New York | accessdate=July 12, 2010}}\n*{{cite web | url=http://www.courts.state.ny.us/history/constitutions/1821_constitution.htm | title=1821 New York Constitution | publisher=The Historical Society of the Courts of the State of New York | accessdate=July 1